gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 98, Magic 74
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeated the Magic, 98-74, as they snapped a five-game win streak for Orlando and jump them in the Eastern Conference standings moving to the four seed. Jalen Brunson led New York with 26 points as Josh Hart (19 points, seven rebounds, four assists) and Precious Achiuwa (15 points, 14 rebounds, four assists, and a career-high five blocks) totaled 34 points. Paolo Banchero led the Magic with 23 points, nine rebounds, and four blocks.
